LAMBDA FUNCTIONS
- One Expressions, Multiple Arguments.
- also called "Anonymous Function" 
- are functions that do not have names
- The result of the expression is totally returned 

//////////
SYNTAX
//////////

lambda arguments: expression 

def add(x+y) : # NORMAL FUNCTION
       return x+y

////////////////////////
SAMPLE LAMBDA FUNCTIONS
////////////////////////

print(add(10,5))

add = lambda x, y: x + y  # Lambda Function
print(add(10,5))# automatically returned

subtract = lambda a, b : a - b
print(subtract(4, 2))
#. ans is "2"
